  "prompt": "What is the best kind of frosting for lemon cake?",
  "response": "There are several great frosting options for lemon cake:\n\n1. Cream Cheese Frosting\n- Tangy and creamy\n- Complements the lemon flavor well\n- Classic pairing with lemon cake\n\n2. Vanilla Buttercream\n- Light and sweet\n- Neutral flavor that doesn't compete with lemon\n- Versatile and widely liked\n\n3. Lemon Buttercream\n- Intensifies the lemon flavor\n- Made with lemon zest and juice\n- Bright and refreshing\n\n4. Swiss Meringue Buttercream\n- Light and silky\n- Less sweet than traditional buttercream\n- Elegant finish\n\n5. Whipped Cream Frosting\n- Light and airy\n- Not too sweet\n- Good for a lighter dessert\n\nThe \"best\" frosting depends on personal preference, but cream cheese and lemon buttercream are often top choices for lemon cake.",
